Sets are used to store multiple items in a single variable.
A set is a collection which is unordered, unchangeable*, and unindexed.

set1={"apple","banana","cheery"}
print(set1)
print(len(set1))
set2={"apple","banana","cheery","apple"}
print(set2)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Access Items
You cannot access items in a set by referring to an index or a key.
But you can loop through the set items using a for loop, or ask if a specified value is present in a set, by using the in keyword.

set1={"apple","banana","cheery"}
for x in set1:
    print(x)
    
print("banana" not in set1)
print("kite" not in set1)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Add Items
By using add and update method

set1={"apple","banana","cheery"}
set1.add("kite")
set2={"dog"}
set1.update(set2)
print(set1)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Remove Items
By using remove, discard, pop, clear and delete

set1={"apple","banana","cheery"}
set1.remove("cheery")
set1.discard("apple")
set1.pop()
set1.clear()
del set1
print(set1)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Join Sets
The union() and update() methods joins all items from both sets.
The intersection() method keeps ONLY the duplicates.
The difference() method keeps the items from the first set that are not in the other set(s).
The symmetric_difference() method keeps all items EXCEPT the duplicates.

set1 = {"a", "b", "c"}
set2 = {1, 2, 3}
set3=set1.union(set2)
set4=set1.intersection(set2)
set5=set1.difference(set2)
set8={'1',"a"}
set6=set1.symmetric_difference(set8)
print(set3)
print(set4)
print(set5)
print(set6)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
